@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
title CIP status lifecycle

[*] --> Draft : opened as a\npull request

Draft : not merged
Draft : aims for a target status

Draft --> Proposed : merged; meets structure,\nquality, technical soundness,\nvalid Path to Active
Draft --> Inactive : rejected or\nabandoned in review

Proposed : accepted design
Proposed : not yet realised

Proposed --> Active : Path to Active met\n(implemented / on mainnet /\nadopted)
Proposed --> Inactive : abandoned, superseded,\nor lost interest

Active : complete, production-ready
Active --> Inactive : superseded by\na later CIP

Inactive : abandoned or superseded
Inactive --> [*]
Active --> [*]

note right of Draft
  There is no "Draft" status
  field; a draft is simply an
  unmerged PR.
end note
@enduml
